cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM. 

The paper presents a new approach for whole image parsing, which is a task related to computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a fully convolutional approach that jointly addresses semantic and instance segmentation tasks, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also reports experimental results on a dataset, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the task of whole image parsing could also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO).
